  "prompt": "What is the processing time for Australian Visa 190?",
  "response": "The processing time for the Australian Visa 190, also known as the Skilled Nominated visa, can vary depending on numerous factors including the completeness of the application, whether all required documents are provided, and the demand for this visa subclass.\n\nAs of my last training data in October 2023, the general processing time can be:\n\n- 75% of applications: 7 months\n- 90% of applications: 10 months\n\nHowever, these times are subject to change and may vary based on individual circumstances and the policies of the Department of Home Affairs. It\u2019s always a good idea to check the latest updates directly from the official Australian Government website or contact the Department of Home Affairs for the most accurate information.",
